    {\displaystyle \alpha =1}
  ) may be beneficial in order to better capture the spread of the distribution and possible nonlinearities. If the true distribution of 
  
    
      
        x
      
    
    {\displaystyle x}
   is Gaussian, 
  
    
      
        β
        =
        2
      
    
    {\displaystyle \beta =2}
   is optimal.

