Discriminative Kalman filter
When the observation model 
  
    
      
        p
        (
        
          
            z
          
          
            k
          
        
        ∣
        
          
            x
          
          
            k
          
        
        )
      
    
    {\displaystyle p(\mathbf {z} _{k}\mid \mathbf {x} _{k})}
   is highly non-linear and/or non-Gaussian, it may prove advantageous to apply Bayes' rule and estimate

  
    
      
        p
        (
        
          
            z
          
          
            k
          
        
        ∣
        
          
            x
          
          
            k
          
        
        )
        ≈
        
          
            
              p
              (
              
                
                  x
                
                
                  k
                
              
              ∣
              
                
                  z
                
                
                  k
                
              
              )
            
            
              p
              (
              
                
                  x
                
                
                  k
                
              
              )
            
          
        
      
    
    {\displaystyle p(\mathbf {z} _{k}\mid \mathbf {x} _{k})\approx {\frac {p(\mathbf {x} _{k}\mid \mathbf {z} _{k})}{p(\mathbf {x} _{k})}}}
  where 
  
    
      
        p
        (
        
          
            x
          
          
            k
          
        
        ∣
        
          
            z
          
          
            k
          
        
        )
        ≈
        
          
            N
          
        
        (
        g
        (
        
          
            z
          
          
            k
          
        
        )
        ,
        Q
        (
        
          
            z
          
          
            k
          
        
        )
        )
      
    
    {\displaystyle p(\mathbf {x} _{k}\mid \mathbf {z} _{k})\approx {\mathcal {N}}(g(\mathbf {z} _{k}),Q(\mathbf {z} _{k}))}
   for nonlinear functions 
  
    
      
        g
        ,
        Q
      
    
    {\displaystyle g,Q}
  . This replaces the generative specification of the standard Kalman filter with a discriminative model for the latent states given observations.
Under a stationary state model

  
    
      
        
          
            
              
                p
                (
                
                  
                    x
                  
                  
                    1
                  
                
                )
              
              
                
                =
                
                  
                    N
                  
                
                (
                0
                ,
                
                  T
                
                )
                ,
              
            
            
              
                p
                (
                
                  
                    x
                  
                  
                    k
                  
                
                ∣
                
                  
                    x
                  
                  
                    k
                    −
                    1
                  
                
                )
              
              
                
                =
                
                  
                    N
                  
                
                (
                
                  F
                
                
                  
                    x
                  
                  
                    k
                    −
                    1
                  
                
                ,
                
                  C
                
                )
                ,
              
            
          
        
      
    
